    "IntroductionThroughout the past century, the education sector has seen transformative technological impacts from technologies such as virtual reality, augmented reality [29], metaverse [31], blockchain [41], simulation learning [39], mobile technologies [1], robotics [2] and drones [42] as well as an online learning environment (Talan & Kalinkara, 2023).",
    "None, however, had as large an impact as generative artificial intelligence, such as ChatGPT, due to its free accessibility and ability to automate communication in response to natural language queries [36].",
    "It reached 1 million users in 5 days [37] and 100 million monthly active users just two months after its launch in January 2023, setting the record for the fastest-growing user application in history [22,23].",
    "While ChatGPT is available in many countries around the world, OpenAI has restricted access to ChatGPT in certain regions, such as Hong Kong, China, Iran, Russia, North Korea and Syria [ 1].Chat Generative Pre-trained Transformer (ChatGPT) is a natural language processing (NLP) model constructed by Open AI in 2019 [49].",
    "It is a kind of generative AI which applies deep learning algorithms to generate human-like text to prompts such as answering questions, programming codes, and generating creative contents [14]."
